oc:kn_0e71df01 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a detected period doesn't match expectations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Period aliasing can cause detected periods to be 2x or 0.5x the true period due to data gaps or missing alternate transits. Always check both period values and examine odd-even transit consistency." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Uneven time sampling creates spectral aliases that masquerade as true periods" .

oc:kn_1a67d92e a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning any exoplanet detection workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The exoplanet detection pipeline has six key stages: Data Loading → Quality Control → Preprocessing → Period Search → Validation → Refinement. Each stage depends on the previous being correctly completed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Skipping stages or executing them out of order leads to false positives or missed detections" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8fa2b2a1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When period search returns no significant candidates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If no significant detection (low SDE): check if preprocessing is removing signal, try less aggressive outlier removal, check for data gaps during expected transits, and consider signal may be below detection threshold." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most failed detections stem from over-preprocessing or data gaps rather than absence of a planet" .

oc:kn_be3fa006 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When one or more planets are already detected and searching for additional planets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For multi-planet systems: find first candidate → mask its transits → search remaining data → repeat until no significant signals remain." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unmasked transits from known planets create spurious peaks that hide weaker additional planets" .

oc:kn_cd8197dd a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When running Transit Least Squares analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "TLS requires flux uncertainties (flux_err) as the third argument — they are not optional. Always include flux uncertainties for proper weighting." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without uncertainties, TLS cannot properly weight data points, degrading detection sensitivity" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_e499f485 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When validating transit candidates from TLS analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "TLS SDE > 9 = very strong candidate, SDE > 6 = strong candidate, SNR > 7 = reliable signal. Low SDE (<6) is a weak signal and likely false positive." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These thresholds are empirically established to separate genuine planetary transits from noise artifacts" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e7c14515 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During quality control stage" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Quality flag conventions vary — flag=0 may mean good OR bad depending on the mission. Always verify the convention before filtering." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incorrect flag interpretation can remove good data or keep bad data, both degrading detection" .

oc:kn_efc16f02 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During preprocessing and trend removal" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not preprocess too aggressively — over-smoothing removes the planetary signal along with the noise. Balance noise removal against signal preservation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Transit signals are shallow (0.01-3% dips) and can be accidentally removed by aggressive detrending or outlier rejection" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f2c28181 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting a period search method" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Choose period search algorithm based on signal type: TLS for transit-shaped (box-like) dips, Lomb-Scargle for general periodic signals and quick exploration, BLS as an astropy-integrated alternative to TLS." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Algorithm choice directly impacts detection sensitivity — TLS is most sensitive for transits but slower; Lomb-Scargle is fast but less sensitive to shallow transits" .

